title: Emmet and Lucyâ€™s Visitors from the Duplo Planet
review:
2/5

It's great to be able to have the Duplo visitors from the movie, but two of them are not the right ones from the ending. It would've been better to have those, but it's still good to have the middle one here. But other than that, there's not much for playability unless you're in the Duplo age range, but even then, there's still not much. Parts are mediocre due to the characters being made of random blocks. The building experience was so quick. The price definitely should've been $5 less.
